{"key":"processedPost-12512918","value":{"id":12512918,"first":12512844,"last":12512918,"when":1273110999,"utime":"05/06/10 04:56 AM","content":"I've found little difference really between shaking immediately and waiting two or three days.&nbsp; <br />My argument for not shaking for a couple of days is based on not disturbing the mycelium that is growing on the wedge.&nbsp; Let it grow off into the grains.&nbsp; When you shake immediately, it disturbs that mycelium, but it doesn't seem to 'rub off' the wedge and into the grains.&nbsp; You still have to wait for the wedge to recover and grow into the grains.&nbsp; Thus you gain a day or two by waiting to shake.&nbsp; It's splitting hairs for sure, but in my experience the hair-splitting is in favor of waiting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Agar in grain"}}